<br>
Personally I would prefer the belt of Virtue as the added AC/STR/WIS/MR outweighs in my mind 5% haste factor.<br>
<br>
Especially coupled with the Valor of Marr 25% self Haste buff we are talking about a difference in haste that will be only a minor hit in the grand scheme of things.  Go with BoV.<br>
<br>
i.e. FBSS and VoM = 46% haste<br>
while BoV and VoM = 41% haste<br>
<br>
Course whats REALLY cool is the Girdle of Faith and Valor of Marr.  That ends up giving you nice stats and a grand total haste of 66% self buffed with VoM <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ucarmaris.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Carmaris</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 179<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/10/02 1:19:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14426.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: belt of virtue or fbss ?</span><hr size=1> I recently snagged Agoroth's Belt of Defense (ac 20 +15 wis/str).  At first I was thinking that it would go well in my wis kit, then looked around and realized that with the Silver Chitin Hand Wraps, this could become part of my standard gear.<br>
<br>
I had been wearing Thunder Etched Gauntlets (ac 20 +4 int +6 str +4 wis +1 PR/DR/CR/FR +2 MR) and FBSS.  Now, I have the Agoroth belt and the Wraps (ac5 +3 all saves), so I've gained 9 str 11 wis +2 PR/DR/CR/FR &amp; +1 MR and 5 raw ac--though I must admit the loss of that 4 int is upsetting <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .  <br>
<br>
The one thing I haven't been able to find out is what the haste % on the wraps is.  I've been told anywhere from 22 - 30%, with most people putting it at the 25 - 27% range.  Anyone have an idea what the actual % is?<br>
<br>
